cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with document representation learning for natural language processing tasks such as sentiment analysis and document classification. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new framework for learning document representations. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper discusses the efficiency of the model in generating representations of unseen documents at test time. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with learning representations for natural language processing tasks, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on developing new algorithms or data structures, but rather on a new framework for learning document representations.
